SUMMARY:Math/Stat Colloquium Series 2025-2026
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Mathematics and Statistics']\\nCategory: Lectur
 e/Panel Discussion\\nCameron McPhee '99Chief Methodologist at SSRS Cameron
  McPhee is the SSRS Chief Methodologist. She provides methodological and s
 tatistical support throughout the organization and designs and implements 
 innovative\, rigorous\, and efficient methods for sampling\, measuring\, a
 nd weighting diverse populations. Cameron directs the SSRS advanced analyt
 ics and methodology team to deliver high-quality\, statistically sound sol
 utions developed using experimentally validated methods.  She creates the
  research and development vision for the organization with respect to surv
 ey methodology and statistical advancement and directs the implementation 
 and dissemination of evolving ideas and strategies. Cameron is also the pa
 st AAPOR Standard’s Chair\, the Past-President of DC-AAPOR\, and a membe
 r of the CNN election night Decision Desk. Cameron has a Master’s degree
  in Survey Methodology from the University of Maryland and a Bachelor’s 
 degree in Feminist Cultural Studies from Swarthmore College.  \\nDetails:
  https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D
 1380668687
LOCATION:Science Center Room 199-Cunniff Hall Tiered Classroom
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1380668687
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Panel Discussion
END:VEVENT
