SUMMARY:Saffran Lecture - Laura Barasa
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Economics']\\nCategory: Lecture/Panel Discussio
 n\\nDepartment of Economics - Saffran LectureLaura Barasa\, Ph.D.Departmen
 t of Economics and Development StudiesUniversity of Nairobi Seeing Develop
 ment from the Other Side Growing up in Kenya\, a lower-middle-income count
 ry in East Africa\, Dr. Barasa saw firsthand how opportunity is shaped not
  only by income\, but also by access to education and good governance. In 
 this talk\, Dr. Barasa draws on her work in development economics to exami
 ne the Global North–Global South divide in both economic outcomes and th
 e production of scientific knowledge. Using examples from research on post
 -election violence\, gambling\, and governance\, she highlights how schola
 rship from the Global South challenges dominant narratives and expands how
  we think about development. This lecture invites us to question whose dat
 a and experiences inform economics\, and how broadening scholarship can op
 en new pathways for opportunity across regions.\\nDetails: https://swatcen
 tral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1361590609
LOCATION:Science Center Room 101- Chang Hou Hall Tiered Classroom
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1361590609
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Panel Discussion
END:VEVENT
