SUMMARY:X-Ray Diffractometer Unveiling Open House Event
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Physics and Astronomy']\\nCategory: Open House\
 \nJoin us in unveiling Swarthmore College’s new X-Ray Diffractometer! An
  X-ray Diffractometer is a powerful instrument that uses X-rays to analyze
  materials and determine how atoms are arranged within them. This instrume
 nt enables researchers from chemistry\, physics\, and engineering to inves
 tigate the structure and properties of a range of materials. Light refresh
 ments will be provided. Location: Science Center Physics Lower Level -  S
 CI L50. Open House Event from 10:00 a.m. - 11:30 a.m.\\nDetails: https://s
 watcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1380668688
