SUMMARY:Denise Bright Dove Ashton-Dunkley: Just Transitions
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Cooper Series']\\nCategory: Exhibit\\nArtist Ta
 lk/Introductory Dinner Friday\, March 20\, 6-8 p.m.  Intercultural Center
 \, Dome Room   Studio Open Hours Monday\, March 23\, 2-4 pm.  TBD   Tra
 ditional Woodcarving Workshop Tuesday\, March 24\, 2-4 p.m.  Makerspace 
   Painting Big Ideas Workshop Wednesday\, March 25\, 2-4 p.m. Kitao Art G
 allery   Studio Open Hours Thursday\, March 26\, 2-4 p.m. TBD   Exhibit 
 opening ceremony Friday\, March 27\, 5-7:30 p.m. Intercultural Center\, Pl
 inth Room   Just Transitions and Land Stewardship on Lenapehoking feature
 s artist Denise Bright Dove Ashton-Dunkley in a weeklong series of worksho
 ps\, open studio hours\, and a monthlong exhibition that uplifts the histo
 ries\, traditions\, and cultural practices of the Nanticoke Lenni-Lenape. 
 Ashton-Dunkley is an award-winning master artisan\, educator\, tribal coun
 cilwoman\, and enrolled citizen of the Nanticoke Lenni-Lenape Tribal Natio
 n of New Jersey\, with over 25 years of experience in the intersection of 
 climate justice\, Indigenous law\, and the arts.\\nDetails: https://swatce
 ntral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1294165005
LOCATION:Hormel/Nguyen Intercultural Center at Sproul Hall Room 107A Plinth
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1294165005
CATEGORIES:Exhibit
END:VEVENT
