SUMMARY:Tri-Co Philly Doughnut Tabling
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ["Provost's Office"]\\nCategory: Training/Worksho
 p\\nCome sample some of Philly's best doughnuts (Beiler's) and learn about
  the Fall 2026 Tri-Co Philly Program. This semester-long program offers st
 udents courses and a host of activities in Philadelphia. Students take two
  urban-focused\, experiential courses taught in Philadelphia\, and also pa
 rticipate in monthly Philadelphia-based activities. Students who will be s
 ophomores\, juniors\, and seniors in Fall 2026 are eligible to apply. FALL
  2026 COURSES | Program students choose 2 of 3 courses\, others can take a
  single course. Ecologies of Cooperation: Modeling Participation and Ecolo
 gical Practice Through Philadelphia-Based Arts\, Culture\, and Environment
 al Co-Operatives | ENVS/VIST H317ABiostatistics: Data\, Health and Ethics 
 in Philadelphia | MATH B195 Art and Culture of Indigenous Philadelphia: F
 rom Shackamaxon to the Present | ARTH061/ENVS056APPLYING TO TRI-CO PHILLY:
   Interested students must attend a Tri-Co Philly Program Student Informat
 ion Session. There is one scheduled at each campus this spring.Haverford: 
 Monday\, March 23\, 2026 | 4:30-5:30 p.m. | Union Building 111Bryn Mawr: M
 onday\, March 30\, 2026 | 4:30-5:30 p.m. | Dalton Hall 025Swarthmore: Wedn
 esday\, April 1\, 2026 | 4:30-5:30 p.m. | SCI 158Online: Thursday\, April 
 2\, 2026 | 7-8 p.m. | Register  After attending one Tri-Co Philly Program 
 Student Information Session\, students can apply for the Tri-Co Philly Pro
 gram. Students unable to attend an information session must meet with the 
 Tri-Co Philly Program director\, Calista Cleary (ccleary1@swarthmore.edu o
 r 610-795-1576)\, prior to applying. The Tri-Co Philly application is due 
 Sunday\, April 5\, by noon. Note: this is before all Tri-Co registration p
 eriods.\\nDetails: https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3D
 event%26eventid%3D1366961318
LOCATION:Sharples Commons - Table 1
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1366961318
CATEGORIES:Training/Workshop
END:VEVENT
