SUMMARY:Tri-Co Philly Student Information Session\, Fall 2026
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ["Provost's Office"\, 'Art and Art History Depart
 ment'\, 'Environmental Studies']\\nCategory: Training/Workshop\\nLooking f
 or a different kind of learning? Curious how your academic work connects t
 o people's lived experience? Come discover the Fall 2026 Tri-Co Philly Pro
 gram\, which connects students to the city. This semester-long program of
 fers students a host of activities in Philadelphia. Students take two urba
 n-focused\, experiential courses taught in Philadelphia\, and also partici
 pate in monthly Philadelphia-based activities. Students who will be sophom
 ores\, juniors\, and seniors in Fall 2026 are eligible to apply. FALL 2026
  COURSES | Program students choose 2 of 3 courses\, others can take a sing
 le course. Ecologies of Cooperation: Modeling Participation and Ecological
  Practice Through Philadelphia-Based Arts\, Culture\, and Environmental Co
 -Operatives | ENVS/VIST H317A | Also counts toward: Growth & Structure of 
 CitiesBiostatistics: Data\, Health and Ethics in Philadelphia | MATH B195 
 | Also counts toward: Data Science\, Health Studies (M-track)\, Growth & S
 tructure of CitiesArt and Culture of Indigenous Philadelphia: From Shackam
 axon to the Present | ARTH061/ENVS056APPLYING TO TRI-CO PHILLY:  Intereste
 d students must attend a Tri-Co Philly Program Student Information Session
 . There is one scheduled at each campus this spring and one online.Swarthm
 ore: Wednesday\, April 1\, 2026 | 4:30-5:30 p.m. | SCI 158Online: Thursday
 \, April 2\, 2026 | 7-8 p.m. | Register  After attending a Tri-Co Philly P
 rogram Student Information Session\, students can apply for the Tri-Co Phi
 lly Program. Students unable to attend an information session must meet wi
 th the Tri-Co Philly Program director\, Calista Cleary\, prior to applying
 .     3. The Tri-Co Philly application is due Sunday\, April 5\, by noo
 n. Note: this is before all Tri-Co registration periods.\\nDetails: https:
 //swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1359415
 741
LOCATION:Science Center Room 158-Classroom
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1359415741
CATEGORIES:Training/Workshop
END:VEVENT
