 eries 2025-2026. This year\, we will focus on Healing and Re-building Co
 mmunity. Facilitated by Dean Tiffany Thompson and Vice President Brooke 
 Vick\, Community Conversations brings diverse community members togeth
 er to discuss\, listen\, and learn from different perspectives. You will h
 ear about other's lived experience and be able to share your own as well. 
 Through open\, honest\, and respectful dialogue\, we will begin building 
 a stronger community.  Fall Semester 2025 September 4th -  Processing 
 our Community's Journey  October 9th  - Repairing Harm: Pathways to Acco
 untability and Reconciliation  November 6th - Shared Values\, Shared Futu
 re: Building a Culture of Trust and Belonging Spring Semester 2026 Februar
 y 5th- Re-imagining Our Campus Community: What Do We Want to Build? March 
 5th - The College’s Role in Campus Healing April 2nd - Allyship and Acti
 on: Moving from Awareness to Impact\\nDetails: https://swatcentral.swarthm
