SUMMARY:Online Tri-Co Philly Student Info Session
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ["Provost's Office"]\\nCategory: Training/Worksho
 p\\nLooking for a different kind of learning? Curious how your academic wo
 rk connects to people's lived experience? Come discover the Fall 2026 Tri-
 Co Philly Program\, which connects students to the city. Students take two
  urban-focused\, experiential courses taught in Philadelphia\, and also pa
 rticipate in monthly Philadelphia-based activities. Students who will be s
 ophomores\, juniors\, and seniors in Fall 2026 are eligible to apply. FALL
  2026 COURSES | Program students choose 2 of 3 courses\, others can take a
  single course (no info session or application needed). Ecologies of Coope
 ration: Modeling Participation and Ecological Practice Through Philadelphi
 a-Based Arts\, Culture\, and Environmental Co-Operatives | ENVS/VIST H317A
  | Also counts toward: Growth & Structure of CitiesBiostatistics: Data\, H
 ealth and Ethics in Philadelphia | MATH B195 | Also counts toward: Data Sc
 ience\, Health Studies (M-track)\, Growth & Structure of CitiesArt and Cul
 ture of Indigenous Philadelphia: From Shackamaxon to the Present | ARTH061
 /ENVS056Tri-Co Philly Program Student Info Session Details | Interested st
 udents should attend an info session.Swarthmore: Wednesday\, April 1\, 202
 6 | 4:30-5:30 p.m. | SCI 158Online: Thursday\, April 2\, 2026 | 7-8 p.m. |
  Register After attending an info session\, students can apply for the Tri
 -Co Philly Program. The application deadline is Sunday\, April 5\, by noon
 . Students unable to attend an information session should meet with the Tr
 i-Co Philly Program director\, Calista Cleary\, prior to applying.\\nDetai
