SUMMARY:SSQL Workshop: Data Visualization in R
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Sociology and Anthropology'\, 'Economics'\, 'Po
 litical Science']\\nCategory: Training/Workshop\\nThis workshop will focus
  on how to visually explore and communicate your data in R. You will learn
  key techniques for creating effective charts and graphs\, choosing approp
 riate visualizations for different types of data\, and interpreting the pa
 tterns you see. We will cover essential packages like ggplot2\, customizin
 g plots\, combining multiple plots\, and best practices for making your vi
 suals clear and informative. By the end of the session\, you'll be able to
  generate publication-quality graphics and use data visualization as a pow
 erful tool for analysis and storytelling.\\nDetails: https://swatcentral.s
 warthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1357216279
LOCATION:Science Center Room 204 - Classroom
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1357216279
CATEGORIES:Training/Workshop
END:VEVENT
