SUMMARY:Pomona: A Play Directed by Montana Hamel
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Drama Board']\\nCategory: Performance\\n POMON
 A: a play directed by Montana Hamel • Friday\, April 10th\, 8pmMartin 0
 13 (Production Studio) • Saturday\, April 11th\, 6pm and 9pmMartin 013 
 (Production Studio) • Sunday\, April 12th\, 8pmMartin 013 (Production S
 tudio)Written by British playwright Alistair McDowall and directed by Mont
 ana Hamel ‘26\, POMONA is a witty\, macabre meditation on the gruesome u
 nderbelly of the corrupt society we inhabit\, which illuminates the sacrif
 ice and humanity that bind us together. As a one-act play\, it confronts t
 he viewer with a non-chronological narrative that highlights the tragedy o
 f each character’s connection to Pomona\, a concrete hole in the middle 
 of the city that is home to the unseen horrors of the elite who profit fro
 m black market trade. For only three nights this April\, come solve the pu
 zzle of Pomona for yourself\, and watch the characters of the play fall vi
 ctim to the loop of fate as they navigate their connections to Pomona\, th
 e law\, the Great Old Ones\, and themselves.  Free and open to the publi
 c. Audience will not need tickets\, first-come\, first-served seating. \\
 nDetails: https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26e
 ventid%3D1380668690
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1380668690
CATEGORIES:Performance
END:VEVENT
