SUMMARY:Inclusive Excellence Lunch & Learns
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Office of Inclusive Excellence'\, 'Be Well']\\n
 Category: Meeting\\nLunch and Learn: Moving Through Conflict with Clarity
  and Care Please join us this academic year for the Lunch and Learn Serie
 s 2025-2026. Focusing on Healing and Re-building Community\, we have invi
 ted Creative Praxis to Swarthmore to guide us through this year's series.
   Creative Praxis is an arts-based\, healing-centered\, and joy-filled 
 training organization. Their programs are designed to inspire and connect 
 people\, fostering personal and community transformation. With over 60 yea
 rs of combined experience\, their facilitators are experts in interactive\
 , transformational facilitation. The founder\, Nia Eubanks-Dixon\, is cert
 ified in restorative practices\, trauma healing\, and de-escalation techni
 ques. September 11th -  Moving Through Conflict with Clarity and Care  -
  An interactive session that challenges the fear of conflict for growth an
 d connection. Learn culturally relevant strategies to navigate conflict wi
 th empathy\, compassion\, and clarity. When conflict is approached with in
 tention\, honesty\, and care\, we strengthen relationships and build healt
 hier communities.\\nDetails: https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmb
 ed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1344954388
LOCATION:Hormel/Nguyen Intercultural Center at Sproul Hall Room 201 Dome Ro
 om
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1344954388
CATEGORIES:Meeting
END:VEVENT
