SUMMARY:Being Well with Sound – Sound Bath (Be Well Community Wellness Da
 y)
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Be Well']\\nCategory: Training/Workshop\\nUnwin
 d on a Friday afternoon with a relaxing sound bath focused on your well-be
 ing with local sound bath practitioner Shaun Collins.  Open to all studen
 ts\, faculty\, staff\, and campus community members. During this soundscap
 e you will be guided along a soothing sound healing journey.From African d
 rumming to Tibetan singing bowls sound has been used to guide and heal th
 e body for centuries! This is a deeply immersive full-body experience wher
 e vibrations are transmitted to your body from various sound healing inst
 ruments. Allowing you to comfortably bask in the waves of harmonic sound.
  All you have to do is simply rest\, be present\, and allow your body to d
 rift along a beautiful soundscape journey. Part of the 2nd Annual Be Well
  Community Wellness Day!\\nDetails: https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?tr
 umbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1380607298
LOCATION:Matchbox Tarble Commons Upper Level
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1380607298
CATEGORIES:Training/Workshop
END:VEVENT
