SUMMARY:SSQL Workshop: Principles of Reproducible Research
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Sociology and Anthropology'\, 'Economics'\, 'Po
 litical Science']\\nCategory: Training/Workshop\\nThis workshop will focus
  on practical methods for making your research transparent\, reliable\, an
 d reproducible. You will learn key techniques for organizing data and anal
 ysis\, documenting your workflow\, and using tools like R Markdown and ver
 sion control to ensure that your results can be easily verified and update
 d. We will cover best practices for sharing data and code\, strategies for
  collaborative research\, and common pitfalls to avoid. By the end of the 
 session\, you’ll have the skills and resources to make your research mor
 e open and trustworthy from start to finish.\\nDetails: https://swatcentra
 l.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1357216283
LOCATION:Science Center Room 204 - Classroom
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1357216283
CATEGORIES:Training/Workshop
END:VEVENT
